description:
Kids and adults agree, these are the Best Sloppy Joes in town.

Directions
Serves 4. 10 min.
Needs: 1 pound ground beef chuck; 1 pouch Red Fork Best Sloppy Joe Skillet Sauce; 1 can (8 ounces) tomato sauce or 1 can (15 ounces) crushed fire-roasted tomatoes.

Stove top:
1. Brown: Cook beef in a 10- or 12-inch nonstick skillet over high heat, stirring often, until nicely browned and cooked, 6 to 8 minutes. 2. Simmer and Serve: Stir in sauce and tomatoes. Simmer gently over low heat, stirring often, about 10 minutes. Season with salt to taste. Serve piled on soft rolls or hamburger buns. Variation: Substitute ground turkey for beef.

description:
Made right with bourbon, garlic and rosemary. Stubb's Cookin' Sauce makes dinner tasty and simple by bringing the legendary flavors of Stubb's into your home.

Directions

Skillet: What You Need: 1.5 lbs. of steak, olive oil and cooked rice or noodles. 1. Rub steak with spice pack. 2. Add 2 tbsp. olive oil to skillet and heat on medium high heat. 3. Cook steak in skillet until your desired doneness (Stubb's recommends following safe minimum cooking temperatures). Add cooking sauce. 4. Let simmer for 15 minutes. Serve with your favorite extras.

Slow Cooker: What You Need: 1.5 lbs. beef roast, beef broth and cooked rice or noodles. 1. Rub beef roast with spice pack. 2. Place beef roast in slow cooker and add 1/2 cup of beef broth. Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours or high for 4-5 hours. 3. After cooking, drain liquid from slow cooker and shred beef with forks. 4. Pour in cooking sauce and heat on low for 10 minutes. Serve with your favorite extras. More Ways to Enjoy: Use chicken, pork, ground beef or shrimp instead of steak or beef roast. Try red wine, chicken broth or water instead of beef broth. Add in extras like mushrooms, onions, green peppers, or sour cream.
title: Stubb's® Cookin' Sauce™ Smokehouse Bourbon 12 oz

Spread both sides of spareribs generously with Ah-So Sauce, place in pre-heated 350 degrees oven and bake larger ribs for 1 hour and 10 min. small ribs for 1 hour.
Chinese pork, chicken and ham:
Spread generously with Ah-So Sauce and roast in oven as usual. Baste occasionally.

Refrigerate after opening.
